  "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nIf you access a Quarkus app on an ipv6 address on a port, like http://[xxxx:xxxx:xxxx......]:8080, and send a Response.seeOther in your jaxrs resource, the ResponseBuilderImpl gets confused by the extra \":\" charecters while trying to extract the port and fails.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nResponseBuilderImpl should correctly parse an IPv6 address\n\n### Actual behavior\n\njava.lang.NumberFormatException: For input string: \"d014:32c:xxxx:xxxx:xxxx:xxxx:xxxx]:8080\"\r\n        at java.base@21.0.2/java.lang.Integer.parseInt(Integer.java:662)\r\n        at java.base@21.0.2/java.lang.Integer.parseInt(Integer.java:778)\r\n        at org.jboss.resteasy.reactive.server.jaxrs.ResponseBuilderImpl.location(ResponseBuilderImpl.java:33)\r\n        at jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response.seeOther(Response.java:713)\n\n### How to Reproduce?\n\nSee description\n\n### Output of `uname -a` or `ver`\n\nLinux ip-172-26-1-8 6.1.0-18-cloud-amd64 #1 SMP PREEMPT_DYNAMIC Debian 6.1.76-1 (2024-02-01) x86_64 GNU/Linux\n\n### Output of `java -version`\n\nopenjdk version \"21.0.2\" 2024-01-16 LTS\n\n### Quarkus version or git rev\n\n2.7.x\n\n### Build tool (ie. output of `mvnw --version` or `gradlew --version`)\n\n_No response_\n\n### Additional information\n\n_No response_",
